The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Fares of AC two-tier and AC first class coaches of several long-distance trains from Howrah and Sealdah will be reduced from Saturday. The trains are the Howrah-New Delhi Rajdhani Express, Sealdah-New Delhi Rajdhani Express, Kalka Mail, Poorva Express, Jodhpur Express, Doon Express, Darjeeling Mail and the Kamrup Express.

 Indian airline has introduced Easy Fare, a promotional scheme fare, on four different levels in certain sectors from Calcutta. The scheme facilitates availability of a level of fare once the lower level becomes full. The scheme will be effective from April 1. 

 he facility has been introduced on the Calcutta-Agartala route where the four levels of fares are Rs 3300, Rs 3,000, Rs 2,721 and Rs 2,221, respectively. For the Calcutta-Nagpur route, the ticket prices of the four levels are Rs 8,000, Rs 7,000, Rs 6,000 and Rs 5,000, respectively. 

 n some sectors, level four of the scheme has been introduced, while the other three levels were revised. On Calcutta-Ahmedabad and Calcutta-Nagpur routes, the fares are Rs 7,220, Rs 6,220, Rs 5,220 and Rs 4,720. The fares are Rs 5,221, Rs 4,721, Rs 3,721 and Rs 3,221 in the four levels on the Calcutta-Dibrugarh route. 

 The American Center library will stay open on Saturdays, between 11 am and 7 pm, from April 1. Special events, including video shows, will be held on Saturdays.

 Justice G.C. Gupta of Calcutta High Court on Friday refused to intervene in the proceedings involving Trinamul Congress councillor Smita Bakshi and the additional district magistrate (ADM), South 24-Parganas. On March 3, the ADM had slapped a notice on Bakshi, asking her to show cause by April 8 why the Scheduled Caste certificate issued to her would not be cancelled. Bakshi had allegedly obtained the certificate by producing forged documents. The court, however, extended the deadline for sending the reply by two weeks.

 Parts of the main block and Block V of the Writers? Buildings were plunged into darkness on Friday morning because of a power cut. Officials said supply was disrupted between 10.55 am and 12.15 pm. The affected areas include a part of the VIP corridor. Power returned 15 minutes before chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee stepped into his office. 

 Seven persons were injured when two private buses collided on Diamond Harbour Road in Bishnupur, on the city?s southern fringes, on Friday morning. The injured were rushed to local hospitals and medical centres. The condition of some of them was stated to be critical.

 Two extortionists were arrested in Baguiati on Friday. Police said Mohammad Yusuf and Mohammad Israfil were picked up following raids in Beraberi (near the airport) and Hatiara areas. 

 A fire broke out in a house in Harachand Mukherjee Lane, under Howrah police station, on Friday morning. A fire brigade official said inflammable articles stored in a room caught fire. One tender fought for half-an-hour to put out the blaze. 

